Troubleshooting & Lessons Learned
Issue 1: APIPA (169.254.x.x) Connectivity Failure
Symptom: Windows Client and Linux Server could not ping each other despite being on the same virtual network.

Diagnosis: Windows defaulted to an APIPA address because no DHCP server was present on the Internal Network.

Resolution: Configured static IPv4 addresses (192.168.10.x/24) for both hosts, forcing them onto the same subnet.

Issue 2: YAML Configuration Errors
Symptom: netplan apply failed with indentation errors.

Lesson: YAML is whitespace-sensitive. Learned to strictly use 2-space indentation levels and avoided the Tab key entirely to ensure configuration validity.

Issue 3: Routing Conflicts (The "Failed to Fetch" Error)
Symptom: Linux server had an internal IP but could not download updates.

Resolution: Implemented a dual-adapter strategy using NAT for external package retrieval and Internal Networking for secure host-to-host communication.
